 :tx/rationale "DAEMON-AS-LIVESTORE-EXTENSION (Session 039): The daemon is not a separate architecture — it's the same LiveStore with a longer lifetime. CLI mode: LiveStore::open() → run_command(&mut live) → live drops (store.bin already written). Daemon mode: LiveStore::open() → loop { socket.accept() → handle_request(&mut live) } → store.bin written on each mutation (crash recovery free). This means: (1) All command implementations work identically in CLI and daemon mode — they take &mut LiveStore, not DiskLayout + Store separately. (2) The daemon's Unix socket protocol is a thin RPC layer over the same command functions. (3) Performance: daemon avoids the 300ms LiveStore::open() on every command because the store stays in memory. Status drops from ~500ms to ~100ms (50ms coherence + 50ms routing). (4) Multi-agent: daemon detects external txn files by watching the txns/ directory (inotify/kqueue). On new external file, reads + applies incrementally. The LiveStore's in-memory state is always the superset of all known txn files. (5) W-alpha integration: the daemon's private working set is a second Store held alongside the shared store. Runtime observations go to W-alpha, not the shared store. (6) The 120+ load_store/write_tx call sites migrate to LiveStore methods, making the daemon a zero-marginal-cost extension rather than a rewrite."
